ExecDesc.value: RealNetworks RealPlayer FLV Parsing Two Integer Overflow Vulnerabilities (IPv6 Version)

EngDesc.value: Two remote code execution vulnerabilities exists in RealNetworks RealPlayer. The vulnerabilities are due to two integer overflow errors while parsing the ECMA Array and the Strict Array type data in FLV files. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability by enticing a target user to open a crafted IVR file. Successful exploitation would allow an attacker to execute arbitrary code in the security context of the logged in user. An unsuccessful attack could cause an abnormal termination of the affected product.
